#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an10.54"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an10.54:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 10 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 10 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.54:0.2"
msgid "6. Sacittavagga "
msgstr "6. Your Own Mind "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an10.54:0.3"
msgid "54. Samathasutta "
msgstr "54. Serenity "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an10.54:1.1"
msgid "“No ce, bhikkhave, bhikkhu paracittapariyāyakusalo hoti, atha ‘sacittapariyāyakusalo bhavissāmī’ti—"
msgstr "“Mendicants, if a mendicant isn’t skilled in the ways of another’s mind, then they should train themselves: ‘I will be skilled in the ways of my own mind.’ "

msgctxt "an10.54:1.2"
msgid "evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabbaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.99, sc2
msgctxt "an10.54:2.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sacittapariyāyakusalo hoti? "
msgstr "And how is a mendicant skilled in the ways of their own mind? "

msgctxt "an10.54:2.2"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, itthī vā puriso vā daharo yuvā maṇḍanakajātiko ādāse vā parisuddhe pariyodāte acche vā udapatte sakaṃ mukhanimittaṃ paccavekkhamāno sace tattha passati rajaṃ vā aṅgaṇaṃ vā, tasseva rajassa vā aṅgaṇassa vā pahānāya vāyamati. "
msgstr "Suppose there was a woman or man who was young, youthful, and fond of adornments, and they check their own reflection in a clean bright mirror or a clear bowl of water. If they see any dirt or blemish there, they’d try to remove it. "

msgctxt "an10.54:2.3"
msgid "No ce tattha passati rajaṃ vā aṅgaṇaṃ vā, tenevattamano hoti paripuṇṇasaṅkappo: "
msgstr "But if they don’t see any dirt or blemish there, they’re happy with that, as they’ve got all they wished for: "

msgctxt "an10.54:2.4"
msgid "‘lābhā vata me, parisuddhaṃ vata me’ti. "
msgstr "‘How fortunate that I’m clean!’ "

msgctxt "an10.54:2.5"
msgid "Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno paccavekkhaṇā bahukārā hoti kusalesu dhammesu: "
msgstr "In the same way, checking is very helpful for a mendicant’s skillful qualities. "

msgctxt "an10.54:2.6"
msgid "‘lābhī nu khomhi ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa, na nu khomhi lābhī ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa, lābhī nu khomhi adhipaññādhammavipassanāya, na nu khomhi lābhī adhipaññādhammavipassanāyā’ti. "
msgstr "‘Do I have internal serenity of heart or not? Do I have the higher wisdom of discernment of principles or not?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an10.54:3.1"
msgid "Sace, bhikkhave, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti: "
msgstr "Suppose that, upon checking, a mendicant knows this: "

msgctxt "an10.54:3.2"
msgid "‘lābhīmhi ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa, na lābhī adhipaññādhammavipassanāyā’ti, tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā ajjhattaṃ cetosamathe patiṭṭhāya adhipaññādhammavipassanāya yogo karaṇīyo. "
msgstr "‘I have serenity but not discernment.’ Grounded on serenity, they should practice meditation to get discernment. "

msgctxt "an10.54:3.3"
msgid "So aparena samayena lābhī ceva hoti ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa lābhī ca adhipaññādhammavipassanāya. "
msgstr "After some time they have both serenity and discernment. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an10.54:4.1"
msgid "Sace pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti: "
msgstr "But suppose that, upon checking, a mendicant knows this: "

msgctxt "an10.54:4.2"
msgid "‘lābhīmhi adhipaññādhammavipassanāya, na lābhī ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassā’ti, tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā adhipaññādhammavipassanāya patiṭṭhāya ajjhattaṃ cetosamathe yogo karaṇīyo. "
msgstr "‘I have discernment but not serenity.’ Grounded on discernment, they should practice meditation to get serenity. "

msgctxt "an10.54:4.3"
msgid "So aparena samayena lābhī ceva hoti adhipaññādhammavipassanāya lābhī ca ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa. "
msgstr "After some time they have both serenity and discernment. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.100, sc5
msgctxt "an10.54:5.1"
msgid "Sace pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti: "
msgstr "But suppose that, upon checking, a mendicant knows this: "

msgctxt "an10.54:5.2"
msgid "‘na lābhī ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa, na lābhī adhipaññādhammavipassanāyā’ti, tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā tesaṃyeva kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ paṭilābhāya adhimatto chando ca vāyāmo ca ussāho ca ussoḷhī ca appaṭivānī ca sati ca sampajaññañca karaṇīyaṃ. "
msgstr "‘I have neither serenity nor discernment.’ In order to get those skillful qualities, they should apply outstanding enthusiasm, effort, zeal, vigor, perseverance, mindfulness, and situational awareness. "

msgctxt "an10.54:5.3"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, ādittacelo vā ādittasīso vā. "
msgstr "Suppose your clothes or head were on fire. In order to extinguish it, you’d apply outstanding enthusiasm, effort, zeal, vigor, perseverance, mindfulness, and situational awareness. "

msgctxt "an10.54:5.4"
msgid "Tasseva celassa vā sīsassa vā nibbāpanāya adhimattaṃ chandañca vāyāmañca ussāhañca ussoḷhiñca appaṭivāniñca satiñca sampajaññañca kareyya. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an10.54:5.5"
msgid "Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tena bhikkhunā tesaṃyeva kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ paṭilābhāya adhimatto chando ca vāyāmo ca ussāho ca ussoḷhī ca appaṭivānī ca sati ca sampajaññañca karaṇīyaṃ. "
msgstr "In the same way, in order to get those skillful qualities, that person should apply outstanding enthusiasm … "

msgctxt "an10.54:5.6"
msgid "So aparena samayena lābhī ceva hoti ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa lābhī ca adhipaññādhammavipassanāya. "
msgstr "After some time they have both serenity and discernment. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "an10.54:6.1"
